     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "TheEulerRotation[{a, b, c}] gives the 2*2 matrix representing the Euler \
rotation, i.e., TheRotation[a, 3] . TheRotation[b, 2] . TheRotation[c, 3] in \
the two-dimensional Hilbert space. TheEulerRotation[{a, b, c}, J] gives the \
Euler rotation in the angular momentum J representation. \
TheEulerRotation[{{a1, b1, c1}, j1}, {{a2, b2, c2}, j2}, ...] is equivalent \
to TheEulerRotation[{a1, b1, c1}, j1]\\[CircleTimes]TheEulerRotation[{a2, b2, \
c2}, j2]\\[CircleTimes] ....", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
